## Processor Portal Deep Analysis

### Pages (via Admin app with role='processor')

| Route | APIs Called | Key Tables | Key RPCs |
|-------|-------------|------------|----------|
| `/` (Dashboard) | `GET /processors/my-stores` | `processor_store_assignments`, `pharmacy` | Direct table access |
| `/warehouse/returns` | `GET /return-transactions` | `return_transactions` | `list_return_transactions` |
| `/warehouse/returns/create` | `POST /return-transactions` | `return_transactions` | `create_return_transaction` |
| `/warehouse/returns/[id]` | Full return lifecycle | `return_transactions`, `return_transaction_items` | All return transaction RPCs |
| `/service-requests` | `GET/POST /processors/service-requests` | `service_requests` | `list_processor_service_requests`, `claim_service_request` |

### Processor-Only APIs

| Endpoint | Tables | RPCs |
|----------|--------|------|
| `GET /processors/my-stores` | `processor_store_assignments`, `pharmacy` | Direct table access |
| `GET /processors/notifications` | - | `list_processor_notifications` |
| `POST /processors/notifications/mark-all-read` | - | `mark_all_processor_notifications_read` |
| `POST /processors/service-requests/:id/schedule` | `service_request_assignments` | `claim_service_request` |

| Portal | Primary DB | Notes |
|--------|-----------|-------|
| **MainAdmin** | Main Admin DB | All MainAdmin tables + warehouse operations + `admin` (buying group accounts) |
| **Admin / Pharmacy / Processor** (combined BG portals) | Main Admin DB (login) → **BG DB** (all operations) | All three portals authenticate via `admin` in Main Admin DB; all operational tables live in the BG DB |

